{
  "_doc": "Phase-5f demo: FIFO + STACK — synchronous queue and LIFO. Click VERILOG to see how each lowers:\n  • FIFO — `reg [W-1:0] mem [0:DEPTH-1]` plus head/tail pointers and a count register. Reads are destructive: when RD is asserted, Q latches mem[head] and head advances. FULL/EMPTY are continuous comparisons against the count. Pointer wrap uses `(p+1==DEPTH) ? 0 : p+1` so non-power-of-2 depths work.\n  • STACK — single SP pointer naming the next-free slot (0=empty, DEPTH=full). PUSH writes mem[sp] then sp++; POP latches Q from mem[sp-1] then sp--. PUSH wins when both asserted.\nBoth use synchronous CLR-priority and parse cleanly through iverilog.",
